02:51.680 --> 02:54.360
<i>♪ When I'm back</i>
<i>on the real scene ♪</i>

02:54.560 --> 02:55.910
♪ ♪

02:56.110 --> 02:59.740
<i>♪ And all the things</i>
<i>that I don't do ♪</i>

02:59.940 --> 03:04.250
<i>♪ Just make me laugh</i>
<i>because they irritate you ♪</i>

03:04.450 --> 03:05.960
♪ ♪

03:06.160 --> 03:08.350
[watch chiming]

03:10.520 --> 03:12.190
Oh, go fuck yourself!

03:14.730 --> 03:16.300
[Shira breathing heavily]

03:16.500 --> 03:19.640
Uh, what are...
what are you doing?

03:19.840 --> 03:20.910
I'm going to school.

03:22.820 --> 03:23.930
Right.

03:24.130 --> 03:25.390
Good.

03:25.590 --> 03:26.790
That's good.

03:28.160 --> 03:31.400
[Mickey] You know,
you look a little red.

03:31.600 --> 03:34.070
It's a...
it's a genetic thing, okay?

03:34.270 --> 03:36.110
From... from exercising.

03:36.310 --> 03:37.490
I didn't even know
you exercised.

03:37.690 --> 03:40.410
You know, what is with
the 800 questions?

03:40.610 --> 03:41.840
I didn't even ask one.

03:43.640 --> 03:44.680
[both giggle]

03:46.470 --> 03:48.330
- You good?
- Yeah, of course. Of course.

03:48.530 --> 03:50.170
Why... why wouldn't I be?

03:50.370 --> 03:52.460
I'll see you at the basketball
pancake thing.

03:52.660 --> 03:54.380
[sighs]
Basketball pancake thing.

03:54.580 --> 03:56.920
Yeah. Yeah. Mm-hmm.
I'll meet you there.

03:57.120 --> 03:58.510
[Mickey] Yeah.

03:58.710 --> 04:00.680
[Shira] All good?

04:00.880 --> 04:01.680
Yeah.

04:01.880 --> 04:02.780
Great.

04:04.740 --> 04:07.140
Yeah.

04:07.340 --> 04:09.270
[sighs]

04:09.470 --> 04:12.270
[soft dramatic music]

04:12.470 --> 04:16.570
♪ ♪

04:16.770 --> 04:18.110
There's no way
they're the same person.

04:18.310 --> 04:19.570
It's the same exact guy.

04:19.770 --> 04:21.160
They even have the same scar.

04:21.360 --> 04:22.320
But how?

04:22.520 --> 04:24.910
There's no way a Nazi
from the 1940s

04:25.110 --> 04:27.540
that killed Bat Lady's dad is
now a paramedic in California.

04:27.740 --> 04:31.540
No, it's just like...
all the retinol in the world

04:31.740 --> 04:33.500
couldn't keep a face
this young, right?

04:33.700 --> 04:34.710
So you don't believe me.

04:34.910 --> 04:35.920
No, I believe
that you believe it.

04:36.120 --> 04:38.220
It's just, like...
it's not possible.

04:38.420 --> 04:39.980
He had a butterfly tattoo.

04:41.360 --> 04:44.560
And my dad recognized him.

04:44.760 --> 04:46.220
[Ema] Yeah, but you only
remembered that,

04:46.420 --> 04:47.600
like, an hour ago.

04:47.800 --> 04:48.660
What?

04:51.580 --> 04:55.230
Mickey, you're just seeing
what you wanna see.

04:55.430 --> 04:57.690
Do you feel the same way?

04:57.890 --> 04:59.700
Um...

04:59.900 --> 05:02.160
yeah, I mean, memory's
a really weird thing, right?

05:02.360 --> 05:03.370
I mean, when I was younger,

05:03.570 --> 05:04.740
I was really
completely convinced

05:04.940 --> 05:06.160
that I was an extra
on <i>The Wire.</i>

05:06.360 --> 05:07.580
But then I got older
and I realized

05:07.780 --> 05:09.160
that I wasn't even alive
when the show came out.

05:09.360 --> 05:11.620
It was a real shock
to my system.

05:11.820 --> 05:12.880
So you both think I'm crazy.

05:13.080 --> 05:14.420
- No. Not at all, Mickey.
- No.

05:14.620 --> 05:16.880
That's not what we're saying
at all.

05:17.080 --> 05:18.460
Sure sounds like it.

05:18.660 --> 05:21.300
Yeah, we're the bad guys,
Mickey,

05:21.500 --> 05:22.510
not the batshit old lady

05:22.710 --> 05:24.010
that thinks
she's Terminator Anne Frank.

05:24.210 --> 05:26.600
She's done nothing
but fuck with you.

05:26.800 --> 05:29.560
Okay. Okay.

05:29.760 --> 05:31.350
I'm just gonna get a photo
for the murder board.

05:31.550 --> 05:32.980
- Oh, come on, man.
- [Spoon] Just for the...

05:33.180 --> 05:35.190
- [Mickey] I'm not...
- You can't get mad at us now.

05:35.390 --> 05:36.860
- We're just being logical.
- Whatever.

05:37.060 --> 05:38.320
[Ema] Where are you going?

05:38.520 --> 05:40.650
We actually have something
really important to show you,

05:40.850 --> 05:42.200
and it's about Ashley.

05:42.400 --> 05:43.990
Wait, yeah, no, you're gonna
shit and piss and throw up.

05:44.190 --> 05:45.490
It's really good.

05:45.690 --> 05:46.970
It's...

05:51.140 --> 05:54.040
[dramatic music building]

05:54.240 --> 06:01.150
♪ ♪

06:06.360 --> 06:07.470
We gotta talk to Rachel.

06:07.670 --> 06:08.890
I'll talk to Rachel.

06:09.090 --> 06:11.310
But Mickey...
Mickey... Mickey...

06:11.510 --> 06:12.830
[Mickey] Send me that video.

06:18.330 --> 06:21.210
That wasn't very nice of you,
Ema.

06:23.340 --> 06:25.110
What, so you believe him?

06:25.310 --> 06:27.450
It doesn't really matter.

06:27.650 --> 06:28.840
We're all friends.

06:31.300 --> 06:32.720
Send me the photo.

06:34.890 --> 06:37.790
[tense music]

06:37.990 --> 06:39.920
♪ ♪

06:40.120 --> 06:41.630
[Mickey] We gotta talk.

06:41.830 --> 06:43.720
Yeah. Of course.

06:43.920 --> 06:44.970
Is everything okay?

06:45.170 --> 06:46.050
[Mickey] I don't know.

06:46.250 --> 06:47.590
Why'd you clear out
Ashley's locker?

06:47.790 --> 06:50.010
Uh, this is actually my locker.

06:50.210 --> 06:51.600
You know
what I'm talking about.

06:51.800 --> 06:53.100
I don't, though.

06:53.300 --> 06:59.310
♪ ♪

06:59.510 --> 07:00.980
Okay, look,

07:01.180 --> 07:02.740
I know you're coming
from a good place and all,

07:02.940 --> 07:04.320
okay, but you need
to drop it, Mickey.

07:04.520 --> 07:06.760
Tell me
what the hell is going on.

07:08.590 --> 07:09.870
Can you just, like,
let this go?

07:10.070 --> 07:11.700
Just let it go.
Please, just trust me.

07:11.900 --> 07:13.660
You know what happened
to Ashley.

07:13.860 --> 07:16.170
Okay, um... um, just meet me
at my house later,

07:16.370 --> 07:17.920
and I'll tell you everything.

07:18.120 --> 07:19.460
- You're kidding, right?
- No, I'm not kidding.

07:19.660 --> 07:21.000
- I'm serious. Not here.
- Fine. When?

07:21.200 --> 07:22.710
I don't know. Like, 6:00.

07:22.910 --> 07:24.380
Troy?

07:24.580 --> 07:25.690
Troy.

07:27.230 --> 07:30.760
- Hi.
- [Troy] Hi.

07:30.960 --> 07:32.890
[Rachel] Look...

07:33.090 --> 07:35.850
I'm really, really sorry
about last night.

07:36.050 --> 07:37.140
Yeah, it was really fucked up.

07:37.340 --> 07:39.020
I know. There's just...

07:39.220 --> 07:40.690
there's just a lot going on
right now.

07:40.890 --> 07:43.030
- Okay?
- Then just tell me about it

07:43.230 --> 07:44.400
rather than freaking
the fuck out at me.

07:44.600 --> 07:45.740
I know. I know.

07:45.940 --> 07:48.450
And what are you doing
talking to Bolitar anyway?

07:48.650 --> 07:50.070
Like, what is hap...

07:50.270 --> 07:54.160
♪ ♪

07:54.360 --> 07:55.620
[Rachel]
Not to be toxic or anything,

07:55.820 --> 07:58.710
but it's really cute
when you get jealous.

07:58.910 --> 08:00.420
- Yeah, I'm always cute.
- [Rachel] Mm-hmm.

08:00.620 --> 08:01.840
[laughs]

08:02.040 --> 08:05.420
♪ ♪

08:05.620 --> 08:06.920
Stop right there!

08:07.120 --> 08:08.530
Get the fuck away from me!

08:11.780 --> 08:13.720
<i>[announcer] Welcome</i>
<i>to the Kasselton High School</i>

08:13.920 --> 08:16.140
<i>basketball</i>
<i>orientation breakfast.</i>

08:16.340 --> 08:17.600
[Buck] My boy!

08:17.800 --> 08:19.730
<i>[announcer] Grab some food,</i>
<i>take a seat,</i>

08:19.930 --> 08:21.150
<i>and we'll be starting</i>
<i>in a minute.</i>

08:21.350 --> 08:23.440
[coughing]

08:23.640 --> 08:25.280
<i>[singer] ♪ Honey ♪</i>

08:25.480 --> 08:26.780
[♪ Plastic Picnic: "Honey"]

08:26.980 --> 08:29.450
<i>♪ Everyone else</i>
<i>you used to know is running ♪</i>

08:29.650 --> 08:32.870
Can I go home now?

08:33.070 --> 08:35.620
[Hannah] What the hump is up,
my Camels?

08:35.820 --> 08:36.750
[cheers and applause]

08:36.950 --> 08:38.850
We love you, Troy's mom!

08:42.390 --> 08:45.750
As Team Mom to this year's
Humping Camels,

08:45.950 --> 08:48.170
I would like to open
by giving a shout-out

08:48.370 --> 08:51.590
to an extra special guest
that we have with us today.

08:51.790 --> 08:53.470
Is it Buck?

08:53.670 --> 08:56.770
- [scattered cheering]
- Uh, no, it is not Buck.

08:56.970 --> 08:58.560
- [laughs]
- Aw, damn it!

08:58.760 --> 09:01.520
[Hannah] This person was
the point guard to my center

09:01.720 --> 09:05.480
and Kasselton Camels'
all-time leading scorer.

09:05.680 --> 09:09.240
Please give a hoofy holler
to my former teammate,

09:09.440 --> 09:11.160
Shira Bolitar!

09:11.360 --> 09:13.070
[applause]

09:13.270 --> 09:15.660
[Shira] Thanks. Thanks.
Thank you.

09:15.860 --> 09:16.950
Thank you.

09:17.150 --> 09:20.250
So, Shira, maybe you have
a few words of advice

09:20.450 --> 09:23.290
for our team about
your time here as a Camel.

09:23.490 --> 09:25.090
Oh, it's completely
unnecessary.

09:25.290 --> 09:26.550
Come on, speech!

09:26.750 --> 09:28.210
[clapping]
Come on, Shira.

09:28.410 --> 09:31.260
Come on up here and show 'em
how it's done.

09:31.460 --> 09:32.680
- Come on.
- [scattered applause]

09:32.880 --> 09:34.640
Whoo!

09:34.840 --> 09:37.780
- Whoo!
- [scattered cheering]

09:40.700 --> 09:43.000
[sighs]
Um...

09:44.120 --> 09:45.110
[groans]

09:45.310 --> 09:46.940
Basketball.
[laughs]

09:47.140 --> 09:49.530
I know, right? Me?

09:49.730 --> 09:52.050
I'm... petite.

09:53.300 --> 09:56.830
But, you know,
I'm... short but mighty!

09:57.030 --> 09:59.870
[crowd muttering]

10:00.070 --> 10:02.370
[exhales]
Uh, yeah.

10:02.570 --> 10:04.790
Uh, I'm here with my nephew,

10:04.990 --> 10:07.520
also really great
at basketball too.

10:10.980 --> 10:12.720
Um, yeah.

10:12.920 --> 10:16.930
So it was a lot of good times

10:17.130 --> 10:18.930
in the gym

10:19.130 --> 10:21.770
and a whole lot of memories.

10:21.970 --> 10:24.770
[soft dramatic music]

10:24.970 --> 10:26.100
♪ ♪

10:26.300 --> 10:28.320
- [person laughs]
- [person] Shh, stop.

10:28.520 --> 10:31.780
♪ ♪

10:31.980 --> 10:32.990
So...

10:33.190 --> 10:37.780
♪ ♪

10:37.980 --> 10:40.910
You will win some,

10:41.110 --> 10:43.220
and you will lose some.

10:46.430 --> 10:50.270
But in the end,
none of that stuff matters.

10:52.020 --> 10:55.260
It's the connections
that you will make

10:55.460 --> 10:57.550
with one another.

10:57.750 --> 10:59.890
That's the stuff that lasts.

