29:59.170 --> 30:01.650
[Ema] I have some matches.

30:01.850 --> 30:03.860
[gasps]

30:04.060 --> 30:06.780
[Mickey] Let's call.

30:06.980 --> 30:10.410
What's the number?

30:10.610 --> 30:14.420
Hi, I'd like to enquire about
a paramedic's assistance

30:14.620 --> 30:15.710
at an accident.

30:15.910 --> 30:17.210
<i>[operator] On which date?</i>

30:17.410 --> 30:19.510
On June 15th.

30:19.710 --> 30:20.710
<i>[operator] Of this year?</i>

30:20.910 --> 30:23.430
Yes. June 15th of this year.

30:23.630 --> 30:25.260
- [phone buzzing]
<i>- [operator] Okay, got it.</i>

30:25.460 --> 30:26.850
<i>- One second.</i>
- Okay.

30:27.050 --> 30:29.070
- [Ema sighs]
- Hold on, one second.

30:31.330 --> 30:32.600
What?

30:32.800 --> 30:34.730
<i>[Spoon] Hey, can you meet me</i>
<i>at the school?</i>

30:34.930 --> 30:36.900
No, I'm busy right now.
What is it?

30:37.100 --> 30:37.940
It's kind of bad.

30:38.140 --> 30:40.860
I'd rather just tell you
in person.

30:41.060 --> 30:42.450
Did you get cut
from the musical?

30:42.650 --> 30:44.820
Ema, the cast list doesn't
go up for another hour.

30:45.020 --> 30:47.120
Why would you put that energy
into the world?

30:47.320 --> 30:49.580
Yes, in Santa Monica, right?

30:49.780 --> 30:52.040
[Ema] Seriously?
I don't have time for this.

30:52.240 --> 30:53.370
Are you sure?

30:53.570 --> 30:56.380
Whatever.
I'll meet you in a few.

30:56.580 --> 30:59.020
- [Mickey] Thank you very much.
- [Ema scoffs]

31:01.400 --> 31:03.470
Holy fuck.

31:03.670 --> 31:04.970
[Ema] What?

31:05.170 --> 31:07.890
That ambulance service didn't
have anyone at that accident

31:08.090 --> 31:10.390
or any accidents that day.

31:10.590 --> 31:13.530
Because one of their ambulances
was stolen the night before.

31:15.830 --> 31:19.500
What the actual fuck
is going on?

31:24.210 --> 31:27.110
[ominous music]

31:27.310 --> 31:33.950
♪ ♪

31:34.150 --> 31:35.260
[shovel thuds]

31:46.860 --> 31:49.760
[ominous music building]

31:49.960 --> 31:56.870
♪ ♪

32:10.170 --> 32:11.470
[Taylor] Jesus.

32:19.600 --> 32:20.980
I'm really sorry, ma'am.

32:23.230 --> 32:24.690
I had to check.

32:26.940 --> 32:28.010
Will that be all?

32:28.210 --> 32:30.640
Yeah.

32:30.840 --> 32:32.100
I'm sorry. I'll just...

32:32.300 --> 32:34.470
Don't.

32:34.670 --> 32:36.890
Don't bother.

32:37.090 --> 32:37.940
Are you sure?

32:38.140 --> 32:40.230
I'm sure.

32:40.430 --> 32:42.020
Goodbye, Ken Taylor.

32:42.220 --> 32:46.280
♪ ♪

32:46.480 --> 32:48.950
What?

32:49.150 --> 32:51.070
You've lived in this town
your whole life.

32:51.270 --> 32:52.800
Of course I know you.

32:55.340 --> 32:57.720
Haven't changed much, have you?

32:59.810 --> 33:02.350
Sorry to have bothered you,
ma'am.

33:10.230 --> 33:13.550
Now Mrs. Kent is missing?
The hell?

33:13.750 --> 33:15.640
Okay, so I don't think
we should jump to conclusions,

33:15.840 --> 33:17.560
but it doesn't feel
like a coincidence.

33:17.760 --> 33:19.140
I mean, maybe the Kents know

33:19.340 --> 33:20.890
more about Ashley
than they're letting on.

33:21.090 --> 33:23.110
Maybe this whole
disappearance thing,

33:23.310 --> 33:25.230
it's just to throw off
the scent, or...

33:25.430 --> 33:27.190
Well, what are we
supposed to do?

33:27.390 --> 33:29.150
Okay, I have a plan.

33:29.350 --> 33:30.740
What plan?

33:30.940 --> 33:32.030
Do you trust me?

33:32.230 --> 33:33.160
No.

33:33.360 --> 33:34.740
Okay, sure.

33:34.940 --> 33:36.660
- [student] No, you deserve it.
- [students chattering]

33:36.860 --> 33:39.410
- [student] Oh, my gosh, yes!
- [Spoon] That's the cast list.

33:39.610 --> 33:40.580
Oh, my God.

33:40.780 --> 33:42.040
Duck and weave,
my short queen, okay?

33:42.240 --> 33:43.580
[Ema] What? Oh, geez!

33:43.780 --> 33:45.630
- I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.
- [Spoon] Sorry, sorry, sorry.

33:45.830 --> 33:47.840
[Ema] Spoon, geez.

33:48.040 --> 33:50.550
- [sighs]
- [Spoon] Ema.

33:50.750 --> 33:52.680
Ema, you're the Phantom.

33:52.880 --> 33:55.800
Oh, my God, Ema,
you're a motherfucking icon.

33:56.000 --> 33:58.810
Oh, your talent, it transcends
all traditional gender roles.

33:59.010 --> 34:00.740
It's incredible. I...

34:03.620 --> 34:04.870
Oh, my God.

34:05.910 --> 34:07.480
Oh, my God, I'm playing Raoul!

34:07.680 --> 34:09.780
Oh, fuck!

34:09.980 --> 34:11.450
Oh, my God,
we're playing enemies.

34:11.650 --> 34:12.780
That's so incredible
because we're friends...

34:12.980 --> 34:14.530
Ms. Friedman obviously
gave me Christine

34:14.730 --> 34:18.620
'cause she knows I have range,

34:18.820 --> 34:23.500
and you're more believable
as a creepy freak, so...

34:23.700 --> 34:26.810
also, I'm not kissing
either of you, so...

34:30.770 --> 34:32.840
Okay, it's not ideal that we're
gonna be fighting over Buck,

34:33.040 --> 34:34.970
but... but... but when you
really break down the show...

34:35.170 --> 34:37.220
I'm not doing it.

34:37.420 --> 34:38.640
No, I mean, you have to do it.

34:38.840 --> 34:39.890
It's, like...
it's part of the story.

34:40.090 --> 34:42.270
No, I'm not doing the play,
Spoon.

34:42.470 --> 34:45.060
Ema, what?
You need to do the show.

34:45.260 --> 34:46.480
Yes, Phantema.

34:46.680 --> 34:49.530
Your audition was insane.
You totally deserve it.

34:49.730 --> 34:52.650
Can't wait to dive
into those cheekbones.

34:52.850 --> 34:54.780
I'm in charge of makeup.

34:54.980 --> 34:57.280
You have, like,
a literal dream canvas.

34:57.480 --> 34:58.830
I mean,
look at those saucer eyes.

34:59.030 --> 34:59.990
Uh...

35:00.190 --> 35:01.290
You should've seen
my brother's face.

35:01.490 --> 35:02.870
It was beautiful.
He was like...

35:03.070 --> 35:04.370
[sighs]

35:04.570 --> 35:06.130
[laughs]

35:06.330 --> 35:09.550
I'm excited to spend
more time with you.

35:09.750 --> 35:12.440
Yeah, it's...
it's gonna be awesome.

35:22.570 --> 35:24.310
Shut up.

35:24.510 --> 35:27.770
It's gonna be awesome, okay?

35:27.970 --> 35:30.020
What's the plan with Mrs. Kent?

35:30.220 --> 35:30.940
[Spoon] Okay.

35:31.140 --> 35:33.820
[sirens wailing]

35:34.020 --> 35:37.110
[intriguing music]

35:37.310 --> 35:40.280
♪ ♪

35:40.480 --> 35:41.870
[Ema]
Spoon, what are you doing?

35:42.070 --> 35:44.620
- This is trespassing.
- [Spoon] Shh.

35:44.820 --> 35:46.870
How the fuck did you get
the key?

35:47.070 --> 35:50.040
Okay, look, never tell a soul,

35:50.240 --> 35:51.380
but I secured it
through this thing

35:51.580 --> 35:54.090
called the Janitorial
Offspring Network.

35:54.290 --> 35:55.840
We trade keys
to places sometimes,

35:56.040 --> 35:58.260
but don't ask me to elaborate
any further, okay?

35:58.460 --> 36:00.300
What happens in the JON
stays in the JON.

36:00.500 --> 36:02.010
- [Ema] Spoon.
- Ema.

36:02.210 --> 36:03.680
You need to stop
asking questions,

36:03.880 --> 36:05.950
or the guild will
have me hanged.

36:09.960 --> 36:11.570
Dr. Kent's office.

36:11.770 --> 36:13.900
Bingo.

36:14.100 --> 36:15.840
[Ema] Did you just say "bingo"?

36:19.130 --> 36:21.580
What are we looking for?

36:21.780 --> 36:22.950
Ties to Ashley.

36:23.150 --> 36:26.210
Signs of... sketchiness.

36:26.410 --> 36:29.420
There's gotta be a reason
why he and his missing wife

36:29.620 --> 36:31.420
were listed
as Ashley's parents.

36:31.620 --> 36:37.770
♪ ♪

36:38.780 --> 36:40.590
Are you gonna help me,
or are you gonna keep on

36:40.790 --> 36:42.010
checking out my ass?

36:42.210 --> 36:45.970
♪ ♪

36:46.170 --> 36:49.100
- I hate you.
- [Spoon] Come on.

36:49.300 --> 36:50.270
Ashley.

36:50.470 --> 36:52.540
Ashley, Ashley, Ashley, Ashley.

36:57.920 --> 37:01.490
Oh, my God, Spoon. Look.

37:01.690 --> 37:03.240
[Spoon] What the fuck?

37:03.440 --> 37:05.010
Dr. Kent was
Dylan Shakes' doctor.

37:09.430 --> 37:11.500
"Abdominal bruising.

37:11.700 --> 37:14.810
Father states patient fell
down the stairs.

37:16.440 --> 37:19.130
Signs of asphyxiation.

37:19.330 --> 37:22.070
Father says
due to a sports injury."

37:24.400 --> 37:26.930
That piece of shit was
abusing Dylan on the regular.

37:27.130 --> 37:29.140
This is so fucking dark.

37:29.340 --> 37:31.140
Everyone always knew
it was the father.

37:31.340 --> 37:34.270
I mean, how is this dude
not in prison?

37:34.470 --> 37:38.400
I don't think they ever could
specifically pin it on him.

37:38.600 --> 37:40.950
But how messed up
is all of this, though?

37:41.150 --> 37:42.410
We have years of proof here

37:42.610 --> 37:44.740
that this kid was
going through hell,

37:44.940 --> 37:47.290
and no one in the town
did shit about it.

37:47.490 --> 37:48.910
How could no one say anything?

37:49.110 --> 37:50.580
I mean, it's all right here.

37:50.780 --> 37:53.710
This is fucked.

37:53.910 --> 37:55.920
Wait.

37:56.120 --> 37:58.800
The last entry doesn't have
anything written.

37:59.000 --> 38:00.420
Oh, my God.

38:00.620 --> 38:04.150
Dr. Kent saw him the day
that Dylan went missing.

38:06.660 --> 38:10.020
[Friedman] Come on. Come on.
Come on, sweetheart.

38:10.220 --> 38:14.190
Good boy. Okay, let's go.

38:14.390 --> 38:16.570
[dog panting]

38:16.770 --> 38:19.570
[tense music]

38:19.770 --> 38:21.110
♪ ♪

38:21.310 --> 38:23.820
[Bat Lady] Hello, Martha.

38:24.020 --> 38:26.300
The police paid me
a visit today.

38:28.260 --> 38:29.790
<i>[chuckles]</i>
<i>They should've dug deeper</i>

38:29.990 --> 38:33.080
<i>to find that scum</i>
<i>rotting in my yard.</i>

38:33.280 --> 38:36.210
You have to stay away
from Mickey Bolitar.

38:36.410 --> 38:39.170
He's still grieving
for his father.

38:39.370 --> 38:40.880
[chuckles]

38:41.080 --> 38:43.800
You think I of all people
don't understand that?

38:44.000 --> 38:47.220
You... you know
what Brad meant to me.

38:47.420 --> 38:50.720
So let his son be.

38:50.920 --> 38:54.730
Why did you photoshop
Luther's face onto that photo?

38:54.930 --> 38:56.150
Him of all people.

38:56.350 --> 38:58.020
You especially
should know better

38:58.220 --> 38:59.940
than to question my methods.

39:00.140 --> 39:03.490
By all means, proceed with your
twisted mind games

39:03.690 --> 39:06.740
and murdering
of drama teachers.

39:06.940 --> 39:08.870
Your Mr. V,
as you so fondly called him,

39:09.070 --> 39:11.160
trafficked in children.

39:11.360 --> 39:13.830
<i>He sold a young girl</i>
<i>for money.</i>

39:14.030 --> 39:15.710
♪ ♪

39:15.910 --> 39:17.170
<i>[Friedman] Ashley Kent.</i>

39:17.370 --> 39:18.670
[Bat Lady] Yes.

39:18.870 --> 39:21.460
And do you know how many other
children suffered and died

39:21.660 --> 39:23.010
because of his greed?

39:23.210 --> 39:26.840
Believe me,
I did the world a favor.

39:27.040 --> 39:31.260
Murder is still murder,
Elizabeth,

39:31.460 --> 39:33.020
no matter how you wrap it up.

39:33.220 --> 39:35.810
[laughs]
There it is.

39:36.010 --> 39:38.020
- What?
- That self-righteousness.

39:38.220 --> 39:41.610
You know, I am surprised
that you still cling to it

39:41.810 --> 39:43.530
after poor Dylan Shakes.

39:43.730 --> 39:45.530
Don't say that name to me.

39:45.730 --> 39:47.240
Do you think
this memorial service

39:47.440 --> 39:49.410
will help relieve your guilt?

39:49.610 --> 39:51.870
You didn't do anything for him.

39:52.070 --> 39:53.660
Get the hell away from me.

39:53.860 --> 39:57.210
♪ ♪

39:57.410 --> 39:59.630
Listen to me.

39:59.830 --> 40:03.840
I'm going to let this one pass
because once we were friends.

40:04.040 --> 40:06.590
We were friends.

40:06.790 --> 40:09.340
But fuck with me again,

40:09.540 --> 40:11.470
and I will put you
in the ground too.

40:11.670 --> 40:18.580
♪ ♪

40:30.510 --> 40:33.080
It's time to talk about Ashley.

40:33.280 --> 40:35.660
♪ ♪

40:35.860 --> 40:37.080
<i>[Rachel] Yay!</i>

40:37.280 --> 40:40.040
I'm gonna need you to stop
staring at your boyfriend.

40:40.240 --> 40:44.000
<i>Ashley came to cheer tryouts,</i>
<i>which you knew already.</i>

40:44.200 --> 40:49.010
She was a good dancer,
but her moves were a bit...

40:49.210 --> 40:51.970
I don't know,
like, a bit risqué.

40:52.170 --> 40:53.760
Okay.

40:53.960 --> 40:58.100
And, well, some of the other
girls started laughing at her

40:58.300 --> 41:01.620
and calling her slutty
and stuff like that.

41:04.250 --> 41:06.460
- Including you.
- No.

41:09.170 --> 41:11.780
No, but I didn't stop them,

41:11.980 --> 41:14.700
and I felt like shit about it
afterwards because, like...

41:14.900 --> 41:16.500
because, like, I'm the captain
and I'm supposed

41:16.700 --> 41:18.460
to make the girls feel
comfortable and safe,

41:18.660 --> 41:21.100
and I didn't do that,
and I felt like I failed her.

41:24.600 --> 41:26.810
<i>So I followed her off</i>
<i>to say sorry.</i>

41:27.980 --> 41:30.130
Ashley?

41:30.330 --> 41:31.430
Ashley.

41:31.630 --> 41:36.850
♪ ♪

41:37.050 --> 41:39.480
[muffled screaming]

41:39.680 --> 41:40.940
[suspenseful music]

41:41.140 --> 41:42.650
Hey! Let go of her!

41:42.850 --> 41:45.150
[both grunting]

41:45.350 --> 41:46.070
Get off! Let go!

41:46.270 --> 41:47.920
[goon] Come on, you gotta go!

41:49.460 --> 41:51.420
- [Rachel yells]
- [grunts]

41:52.920 --> 41:54.570
Shoot her!

41:54.770 --> 41:56.490
[goon] No, we need her alive.

41:56.690 --> 41:57.660
Let's get outta here. Come on!

41:57.860 --> 42:00.660
♪ ♪

42:00.860 --> 42:03.770
[tires squealing]

42:04.890 --> 42:06.290
Are you okay?

42:06.490 --> 42:08.050
We have to get out of here.

42:08.250 --> 42:09.510
[breathing heavily]

42:09.710 --> 42:11.480
They found me.

42:15.320 --> 42:16.850
Ashley, who were those guys?

42:17.050 --> 42:19.020
I don't wanna tell you.

42:19.220 --> 42:21.060
I just feel like
the less you know, the better.

42:21.260 --> 42:23.230
We have to go to the police.

42:23.430 --> 42:24.650
You know that, right?
You're just a kid.

42:24.850 --> 42:25.900
Whatever it is
you're worried about,

42:26.100 --> 42:27.690
you're not gonna get
in trouble, I promise.

42:27.890 --> 42:31.070
Please, Rachel, no police.

42:31.270 --> 42:33.110
They're in on it too. Please.

42:33.310 --> 42:35.410
Okay, okay, okay.

42:35.610 --> 42:39.040
No police, but, like,
what can I do to help you?

42:39.240 --> 42:42.310
You can't.
They'll kill you, Rachel.

42:44.140 --> 42:45.710
I have to get out of Kasselton.

42:45.910 --> 42:47.630
That's what I have to do.
I have to leave.

42:47.830 --> 42:48.960
Come stay at my house.

42:49.160 --> 42:50.460
- Fuck no.
- Yes. Yes.

42:50.660 --> 42:52.090
My dad's always away.
He travels for work.

42:52.290 --> 42:54.430
No one's gonna be home.
No one else has to know.

42:54.630 --> 42:57.550
Okay? And you'll be safe there.

42:57.750 --> 42:59.180
Please. Please let me help you.

42:59.380 --> 43:00.720
You don't have to do this,
Rachel.

43:00.920 --> 43:03.390
I know, but I want to, okay?
I want to.

43:03.590 --> 43:06.400
[soft dramatic music]

43:06.600 --> 43:07.730
♪ ♪

43:07.930 --> 43:09.480
Wait.

43:09.680 --> 43:11.780
So Ashley's here right now.

43:11.980 --> 43:14.210
Yeah, she's in the pool house.

43:15.800 --> 43:19.950
[clattering]

43:20.150 --> 43:21.330
[phone alarm beeping]

43:21.530 --> 43:23.120
[Rachel] Wait, wait.
Mickey, don't go outside.

43:23.320 --> 43:24.960
- What?
- Someone's here.

43:25.160 --> 43:26.920
[suspenseful music]

43:27.120 --> 43:28.630
Fuck.

43:28.830 --> 43:30.840
Call 911.

43:31.040 --> 43:33.800
Um... fuck, I don't have
a signal.

43:34.000 --> 43:36.010
I don't have a signal.

43:36.210 --> 43:39.550
♪ ♪

43:39.750 --> 43:42.070
Fuck. This one's dead too.

43:44.080 --> 43:45.890
Fuck!

43:46.090 --> 43:53.000
♪ ♪

43:56.340 --> 43:57.710
He's here for Ashley.

43:59.760 --> 44:01.050
Mickey, no!

45:26.390 --> 45:29.350
[lion roars]
